4. Check network connectivity for model loading3. Verify Prisma schema migration was successful2. Review WebView console logs1. Check Ready Player Me's documentationFor issues or questions:## Support- [WebView Flutter Package](https://pub.dev/packages/webview_flutter)- [Model Viewer Plus Package](https://pub.dev/packages/model_viewer_plus)- [Ready Player Me Documentation](https://docs.readyplayer.me/)## Resources- [ ] Export avatar as image for sharing- [ ] Avatar accessories shop- [ ] Share avatar customizations- [ ] Avatar-based achievements/badges- [ ] Use avatars in workout animations- [ ] Display avatars in community/social featuresPossible future improvements:## Future Enhancements6. **Lightweight**: Models are optimized for mobile performance5. **AR Ready**: Avatars can be viewed in AR (Augmented Reality)4. **Cross-Platform**: Works on iOS, Android, and Web3. **Professional Quality**: Ready Player Me provides high-quality 3D models2. **Highly Detailed**: Every aspect of the avatar can be customized1. **Snapchat-like Experience**: Familiar, intuitive avatar creation## Benefits```}  }    // Additional configuration    "avatarId": "...",    "url": "https://models.readyplayer.me/...",  "data": {  "eventName": "v1.avatar.exported",{```jsonThe integration listens for the `v1.avatar.exported` event which contains:### Event Handling- `language`: Set creator language- `quickStart`: Skip intro animation- `bodyType`: Choose between 'fullbody' or 'halfbody'- `clearCache`: Clear previous avatar data- `frameApi`: Enable message passing between web and native### Query Parameters## Ready Player Me Configuration```showAvatarDialog(context, user.avatarUrl!, is3D: true);// Fullscreen view)  is3D: true,  size: 150,  avatarUrl: user.avatarUrl,AvatarViewer(// Large avatar (e.g., in profile))  is3D: true,  size: 50,  avatarUrl: user.avatarUrl,AvatarViewer(// Small avatar (e.g., in lists)import '../widgets/avatar_viewer.dart';```dartTo display a user's avatar anywhere in the app:#### Integration in Other Screens   ```   };     'language': 'en',     'quickStart': 'false',     'bodyType': 'fullbody',  // or 'halfbody'     'clearCache': 'true',     'frameApi': 'true',   final queryParams = {   ```dart   Modify query parameters in `_initializeWebView()`:2. **Customization Options**   ```   final subdomain = 'demo'; // Replace with your subdomain   ```dart   In `avatar_creator_screen.dart`, update the subdomain:1. **Ready Player Me Subdomain**#### Configuration### For Developers   - Save to update   - Make changes in Ready Player Me creator   - Tap "Edit 3D Avatar" button in profile3. **Editing Your Avatar**   - Auto-rotate mode available   - Rotate and zoom to see details   - Tap avatar to view in fullscreen   - 3D avatar displays in profile header2. **Viewing Your Avatar**   - Avatar automatically appears in your profile   - Save when satisfied   - Customize your avatar in the Ready Player Me creator   - Tap "Create 3D Avatar" button   - Go to Profile screen1. **Creating an Avatar**### For Users## Usage   - Tap on 3D avatar to view in fullscreen with rotation   - Shows 3D avatar when available, falls back to 2D image   - Integrated `AvatarViewer` widget   - Added "Create 3D Avatar" button3. **`lib/screens/profile_screen.dart`**   - Handles both traditional avatar images and Ready Player Me avatars   - Added `rpmAvatarUrl` and `avatarConfig` parameters to `updateProfile()`2. **`lib/services/profile_service.dart`**   - Updated serialization methods   - Added `avatarConfig` field for avatar configuration   - Added `avatarUrl` field for Ready Player Me URL1. **`lib/models/user.dart`**#### Modified Files   - Fullscreen dialog view with AR support   - Interactive 3D viewing with auto-rotate   - Supports both 3D GLB models and 2D images   - Displays 3D avatars using ModelViewer2. **`lib/widgets/avatar_viewer.dart`**   - Full-screen immersive experience   - Saves avatar URL and config to backend   - Handles avatar export events   - WebView implementation of Ready Player Me avatar creator1. **`lib/screens/avatar_creator_screen.dart`**#### New Files```  model_viewer_plus: ^1.8.0       # For displaying 3D avatars  webview_flutter: ^4.10.0        # For embedding Ready Player Me creatordependencies:```yaml#### New Dependencies (`pubspec.yaml`)### Mobile App Changes- `avatarConfig`: JSON configuration with avatar customization details- `avatarUrl`: The GLB model URL from Ready Player MeThe existing profile update endpoint (`PATCH /auth/profile`) now accepts:#### API Endpoints```}  avatarConfig Json?       // Avatar customization config from Ready Player Me  avatarUrl    String?     // Ready Player Me avatar URL (GLB model)  // ... existing fieldsmodel User {```prismaAdded two new fields to the User model in `prisma/schema.prisma`:#### Database Schema### Backend Changes## Technical Implementation- ✅ **Profile Integration**: Avatars are prominently displayed in user profiles- ✅ **Backend Storage**: Avatar URLs and configuration are stored in the database- ✅ **WebView Integration**: Uses Ready Player Me's web-based creator in a native WebView- ✅ **3D Model Display**: Avatars are rendered as interactive 3D models using `model_viewer_plus`  - Body type  - Clothing and accessories  - Facial hair  - Eye color and shape  - Hairstyle and color  - Skin tone  - Face shape and features- ✅ **Detailed Avatar Customization**: Users can customize every aspect of their avatar:## FeaturesUsers can create highly customizable 3D avatars using Ready Player Me's avatar creator, similar to Snapchat's Bitmoji. These avatars are stored as GLB 3D models and can be displayed throughout the app.## OverviewThis document explains how the Ready Player Me 3D avatar system is integrated into the mobile app.import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
